Bitwise Operators
1) And (&) 
  . All True - True 
  . One False - False   
2) OR(|)
  .One True - True 
  .All False - False 
3) XOR(^)
  . No of one's even - 0 
  . No of one's odd - 1 
4)Right Shift 
  . X>>K (X is a number and K is no of shifts) 
  .Formula :-   X//(2**(K)) 
5)Left Shift 
  .X<<K(X is number and K is no of shifts)
  .Formula :- x*(2**(k))
6)Not Operator 
  .Flip 
  .If -ve 
      .2s compliment 
      .Stop     
  .Formula :- ~x = -(x + 1)      
